===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*rīk-, *rīkja-'', from Celtic ''*rīgiom'' ‘kingdom’, from ''*rīgs'' ‘king’ (Old Irish [[rí]]), from Indo-European ''*rēgs'' ‘king’.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[riki|rīki]] (Dutch [[rijk]] ''n'' & ''adj''), Old High German [[rihhi|rīhhi]] (German [[Reich]] ''n'', [[reich]] ''adj''), Old Norse [[riki|ríki]] ''n'', [[rikr]] ''adj'' (Swedish [[rike]] ''n'', [[rik]] ''adj''), Gothic [[𐍂𐌴𐌹𐌺𐌹]] ''n'', [[𐍂𐌴𐌹𐌺𐌴𐌹𐍃]] ''adj''.  The IE root is also the source of Latin [[rex]].

